The paper focuses on developing a toolset for learning from, understanding, and supporting developers writing DevOps artifacts, specifically Dockerfiles. This involves addressing challenges related to nested languages, rule mining, and semantic rule-based analysis. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category, as it deals with developing tools and techniques to support software development. Additionally, the paper involves parsing and analyzing code, which falls under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel rule-mining technique and uses machine learning to identify best practices, which falls under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with security and reliability issues related to Dockerfiles, which falls under the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves developing a toolset for analyzing and improving existing systems, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
